WEBVTT

00:05.000 --> 00:07.420
♪ Magic is real here ♪

00:07.500 --> 00:10.000
♪ Far away from home ♪

00:10.090 --> 00:12.420
♪ Anything can happen ♪

00:12.510 --> 00:15.390
♪ When witches make the rules ♪

00:15.470 --> 00:17.760
♪ Monsters are cool ♪

00:17.850 --> 00:20.770
♪ The moon is our friend ♪

00:20.850 --> 00:23.100
♪ I wanna stay with you ♪

00:23.180 --> 00:27.230
♪ On Summer Camp Island ♪

00:29.520 --> 00:35.110
♪♪

00:35.200 --> 00:37.120
[ Sighs ]

00:37.200 --> 00:39.660
Dear Diary...

00:39.740 --> 00:42.120
Ramona left today
to go live in frozen time,

00:42.200 --> 00:44.250
and...

00:44.330 --> 00:46.420
I feel fine about it.

00:46.500 --> 00:47.630
Not sad at all.

00:47.710 --> 00:49.380
If anything, I could use
a break from her.

00:49.460 --> 00:52.460
Sometimes best friends need
to not be together, you know?

00:52.550 --> 00:54.380
I couldn't help but wonder
though,

00:54.470 --> 00:57.220
what do I do
with her raggedy pajamas?

00:57.300 --> 00:59.800
Throw them away?
Use them for scraps?

00:59.890 --> 01:01.310
Scarecrow, perhaps?

01:01.390 --> 01:03.310
Hey, I'm right here!

01:03.390 --> 01:05.640
Yeah, well I need you
to be right here!

01:05.730 --> 01:07.650
Ugh.

01:10.570 --> 01:13.360
[ Grunts ]
Can I get a little help?

01:13.440 --> 01:14.990
Mm...no.

01:15.070 --> 01:17.160
[ Grunting ]

01:17.240 --> 01:19.660
What are you, a redwood tree,
General Sherman?

01:19.740 --> 01:21.870
Ramona used to help me
with this, ya know?

01:21.950 --> 01:25.000
I need to conserve my energy
for sleeping.

01:25.080 --> 01:27.920
Ugh, is that why you don't
brush your teeth?

01:28.000 --> 01:29.710
I don't need
to brush my teeth.

01:29.790 --> 01:32.050
[ Grunting ]

01:32.130 --> 01:33.460
We don't fit.

01:33.550 --> 01:35.590
I'm a Ramona size only.

01:35.670 --> 01:40.180
♪♪

01:40.260 --> 01:41.680
Well, it looks like things
have changed

01:41.760 --> 01:44.060
and you don't suit
each other anymore.

01:45.890 --> 01:48.020
Now, let's put all this
to bed already.

01:48.100 --> 01:50.860
♪♪

01:50.940 --> 01:52.440
Can you leave
the lights on?

01:52.520 --> 01:54.730
I'm scared of the dark.

01:54.820 --> 01:57.110
Hey -- ugh -- come on!
That's just rude.

01:57.200 --> 01:58.400
[ Knock on door ]

01:58.490 --> 02:00.240
Ugh, what is it now!

02:02.280 --> 02:04.370
This better
be important.

02:04.450 --> 02:06.500
Susie!
Susie?

02:06.580 --> 02:08.540
Alice, do you know
what time it is?

02:08.620 --> 02:10.210
I am not in the mood
for "Light as a Feather,

02:10.290 --> 02:11.710
Stiff as a Board"
even though it looks like

02:11.790 --> 02:13.800
I'm am literally begging you
to play with me.

02:13.880 --> 02:17.630
Susie, something very strange
happened to me.

02:17.720 --> 02:20.640
I was falling asleep thinking
about my recent immortality

02:20.720 --> 02:22.850
and how I could
never go home again,

02:22.930 --> 02:25.680
how I'll never sit on my roof
eating frozen grapes

02:25.770 --> 02:28.230
while listening
to distant train horns,

02:28.310 --> 02:32.110
and then I burped and a ghost
came out of my mouth!

02:32.190 --> 02:33.650
It started waxing poetic

02:33.730 --> 02:36.860
about scuppernongs versus
Concord grapes and longing,

02:36.940 --> 02:40.860
and then it just
evaporated into nothing.

02:40.950 --> 02:42.030
Am I cursed?

02:42.120 --> 02:44.950
Is immortality a curse?

02:45.030 --> 02:46.740
Is this my life now?

02:46.830 --> 02:48.620
Oh, no!
[ Sobbing ]

02:48.710 --> 02:52.210
My goodness! Does no one brush
their teeth around here?

02:52.290 --> 02:54.380
No, Alice,
you're not cursed.

02:54.460 --> 02:55.670
Huh?

02:55.750 --> 02:57.920
Look, when you're immortal,
your memories and regrets

02:58.010 --> 03:00.840
sometimes slip out
when you burp, as ghosts.

03:00.930 --> 03:02.430
The more traumatizing ones
stick around,

03:02.510 --> 03:04.430
but the lighter ones
will just evaporate.

03:04.510 --> 03:07.350
Buy a bottle of seltzer and you
can bypass years of therapy.

03:07.430 --> 03:09.100
Wow, we burp ghosts.

03:09.180 --> 03:10.770
That must happen to you
all the time then.

03:10.850 --> 03:12.980
You've been around
for centuries.

03:13.060 --> 03:15.650
Uh, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no.

03:15.730 --> 03:18.320
I'm not haunted by any
recollections of the past.

03:18.400 --> 03:20.530
I'm perfectly well-adjusted.
Thank you.

03:20.610 --> 03:22.070
Pfft.

03:22.160 --> 03:24.990
What about earlier today?
When your best friend left you?

03:25.070 --> 03:27.290
We all saw.
[ Gasps ]

03:27.370 --> 03:29.080
Do you have to burp?

03:29.160 --> 03:30.710
Nope!

03:30.790 --> 03:33.290
No burps here!

03:33.370 --> 03:34.790
Okay, good night!

03:34.880 --> 03:38.090
Okay!
Night, Susie.

03:38.170 --> 03:45.260
♪♪

03:45.350 --> 03:47.180
Oh, hey, Susie!

03:47.260 --> 03:49.810
Um, do you still have
that amulet I lent you?

03:49.890 --> 03:53.390
'Cause it turns out my grandma's
trapped in it, and...

03:54.650 --> 03:58.070
Okay, you could just
hold onto it for now.

03:58.150 --> 03:59.690
[ Grunting ]

03:59.780 --> 04:02.570
♪♪

04:02.650 --> 04:04.990
[ Gasps, continues grunting ]

04:05.070 --> 04:15.000
♪♪

04:15.080 --> 04:18.000
[ Burping ]

04:18.090 --> 04:19.710
[ Sighs ]

04:19.800 --> 04:21.840
Tissue?
Huh?

04:23.220 --> 04:25.970
Hiya!
Where's Ramona?

04:26.050 --> 04:27.640
Perfectly...

04:27.720 --> 04:29.390
well-adjusted.

04:32.350 --> 04:34.600
Well.
Get on then. Off you go.

04:34.690 --> 04:36.770
Go?
Where am I going?

04:36.850 --> 04:38.980
Either you dissolve into mist
or float off

04:39.070 --> 04:41.360
or find some swampy
nook to occupy.

04:41.440 --> 04:43.240
That sounds depressing.

04:43.320 --> 04:45.610
You're a sad memory.
What do you expect?

04:45.700 --> 04:47.030
You stick to your side
of the street,

04:47.120 --> 04:48.450
and I'll stick to mine.

04:48.530 --> 04:50.740
Hmm.

04:50.830 --> 04:52.450
I think I'm gonna
stay with you.

04:52.540 --> 04:55.420
Forever!
Unlike somebody I can name.

04:55.500 --> 04:57.290
And it rhymes with lasagna.

04:57.380 --> 04:58.880
Actually not really.

04:58.960 --> 05:00.840
It's Ramona!
No!

05:00.920 --> 05:04.470
Staying with me was not listed
as an option!

05:04.550 --> 05:06.260
You could start
a ghost business,

05:06.340 --> 05:08.220
invest in ghost
real estate.

05:08.300 --> 05:12.220
You can even go to school,
get a little ghost diploma.

05:12.310 --> 05:13.980
Boring!
I'd rather tell you

05:14.060 --> 05:16.310
all my thoughts
and feelings about loss.

05:16.390 --> 05:19.400
Or<i> our</i> thoughts and feelings,
am I right?

05:19.480 --> 05:21.070
No.
I burped you out.

05:21.150 --> 05:24.240
Now, just thank me and get on
with the dissipating.

05:24.320 --> 05:27.530
Good eve to you.

05:27.610 --> 05:29.240
Whoa!

05:29.320 --> 05:33.370
♪♪

05:33.450 --> 05:35.460
[ Gasps ]
How did you get here?

05:35.540 --> 05:37.920
Oh, hi, Susie.
Welcome back.

05:38.000 --> 05:39.880
I made you
garlic ghost toast.

05:39.960 --> 05:42.380
No!
No garlic for her, please!

05:42.460 --> 05:44.420
-Ah!
-Thanks but no.

05:44.510 --> 05:46.920
You can't be here.

05:47.010 --> 05:48.130
Huh?

05:48.220 --> 05:49.840
Whoa!

05:52.350 --> 05:53.930
Oh, that's better.

05:54.020 --> 05:55.850
Now to get some sleep finally.

05:59.940 --> 06:02.480
Don't you think you're being
a little harsh on him?

06:02.570 --> 06:05.860
He is my unresolved feelings
about my recent friend rupture.

06:05.940 --> 06:08.820
I can do with him
as I please.

06:08.910 --> 06:11.570
[ Grunting ]

06:13.030 --> 06:14.450
Why can't I sleep?

06:14.540 --> 06:16.120
-Hey, Susie!
-Aah!

06:16.200 --> 06:18.290
I was thinking we could stay up
all night and replay

06:18.370 --> 06:21.250
in tormenting detail the exact
moment you found out things

06:21.330 --> 06:23.540
were gonna change between you
and your best friend, Ramona.

06:23.630 --> 06:25.000
That even if you still
got to see her...

06:25.090 --> 06:26.590
-Why won't he leave you alone?
-I don't know.

06:26.670 --> 06:28.130
This has never
happened before!

06:28.220 --> 06:29.470
Well get rid of him!

06:29.550 --> 06:31.300
What do you think
I'm trying to do?

06:31.390 --> 06:33.180
...could change.

06:33.260 --> 06:35.260
That a loss like this
is on the table

06:35.350 --> 06:37.180
even though the friendship
had previously

06:37.270 --> 06:39.850
made you feel protected
from loss at this scale.

06:39.940 --> 06:42.020
Susie, you can't
ghost him forever.

06:42.110 --> 06:44.150
Ohh, fine!

06:44.230 --> 06:46.030
You're coming with me!

06:46.110 --> 06:47.780
It worked!

06:51.410 --> 06:53.870
-Hi, Dad.
-Susie!

06:53.950 --> 06:55.370
Hi, sweetie!

06:55.450 --> 06:58.160
Hi, other dad.

06:58.250 --> 07:00.290
Okay, that's enough
sentimentality.

07:00.370 --> 07:02.580
What can we do for ya,
Pumpernickel?

07:02.670 --> 07:05.040
Well, this.

07:07.550 --> 07:09.380
Hey, come meet these guys.

07:09.470 --> 07:12.300
This one is a memory of my dad,
and so is this.

07:12.390 --> 07:14.850
They're very nurturing and
willing to talk about whatever.

07:14.930 --> 07:16.100
They're your dads now.

07:16.180 --> 07:18.470
-Yeah! We're dads!
-Yeah! We're dads!

07:18.560 --> 07:20.730
Just what every dad
really needs.

07:20.810 --> 07:21.980
A kid!

07:22.060 --> 07:23.190
Aw.

07:23.270 --> 07:24.480
[ Laughter ]

07:24.560 --> 07:27.190
Congratulations on
your beautiful family.

07:27.280 --> 07:28.690
Okeydokey.

07:30.440 --> 07:31.780
Ah, no, you don't!

07:31.860 --> 07:33.910
You stay with them.
You live here in that tree.

07:33.990 --> 07:36.200
You eat toasts
with your fellow ghosts!

07:36.280 --> 07:38.240
Ugh, now I'm rage rhyming.

07:38.330 --> 07:39.700
Dads, help!

07:39.790 --> 07:42.420
-[ Laughing ]
-Whoo! We're gonna be dads!

07:42.500 --> 07:44.710
Huh?

07:44.790 --> 07:46.090
What's wrong, Ghost?

07:46.170 --> 07:48.250
Don't you want to live
with us in the swamp?

07:48.340 --> 07:49.760
It's what us ghosts do.

07:49.840 --> 07:51.380
It's just...

07:51.470 --> 07:54.050
I really want to talk
to Susie is all.

07:54.140 --> 07:55.970
Plus, it's kind of
creepy here.

07:56.050 --> 07:57.260
Ugh.

07:57.350 --> 07:59.100
Well, what if we showed
you around a bit?

07:59.180 --> 08:00.930
So you could get a sense
of the place?

08:01.020 --> 08:03.310
Who wants to call
a strange place home, right?

08:03.390 --> 08:06.900
-Can Susie come?
-Sure! Right, Suze?

08:06.980 --> 08:09.230
Ugh, do I have to?

08:09.320 --> 08:11.110
Susie...

08:11.190 --> 08:12.860
Oh, fine.

08:14.990 --> 08:17.070
And that's an old,
rotted log.

08:17.160 --> 08:19.240
And there's a bunch of moss
draped over a branch.

08:19.330 --> 08:20.700
And look, son.

08:20.790 --> 08:24.870
A raven who looks like
he knows a terrible secret.

08:24.960 --> 08:27.290
Oh! Look!

08:27.380 --> 08:29.090
Dead and Breakfast?

08:29.170 --> 08:30.420
Oh, we're not really dead.

08:30.500 --> 08:32.380
That's a common
misconception.

08:32.470 --> 08:34.010
We play into it.

08:34.090 --> 08:36.260
We got tired of explaining
that we're burps.

08:36.340 --> 08:38.050
Oh!
And look there.

08:38.140 --> 08:41.430
This place has really good
mashed potato milkshakes.

08:41.520 --> 08:43.560
Remember when you drank
so many of those,

08:43.640 --> 08:45.940
Susie, and we had
to roll you out of there?

08:46.020 --> 08:47.690
That didn't happen!

08:47.770 --> 08:50.230
Yes it did.

08:50.320 --> 08:52.110
Okay, okay.
Nothing to see here.

08:52.190 --> 08:55.030
♪♪

08:55.110 --> 08:56.990
Oh, wow!
A carousel.

08:57.070 --> 09:02.290
♪♪

09:02.370 --> 09:04.410
Do you want to ride
the carousel, Son?

09:04.500 --> 09:06.540
No, thanks, Dad.
I'm too old.

09:06.620 --> 09:08.920
Yeah, me, too.

09:09.000 --> 09:10.960
Let's go do something
for grown-ups.

09:11.050 --> 09:13.420
♪♪

09:13.510 --> 09:15.050
Welcome to Plymouth Rock.

09:15.130 --> 09:17.430
Are you now,
or have you ever been

09:17.510 --> 09:19.050
a witch?

09:19.140 --> 09:22.600
♪♪

09:22.680 --> 09:24.350
Hi, corn girl.

09:24.430 --> 09:26.480
Nice haircut!

09:26.560 --> 09:28.190
Pbht!

09:28.270 --> 09:30.690
[ Laughter ]

09:34.740 --> 09:36.780
On Wednesday nights,
we come to this piano bar

09:36.860 --> 09:38.450
for "Wednesdays
with Weepy,"

09:38.530 --> 09:40.490
one of
Susie's saddest burps.

09:40.570 --> 09:45.000
♪♪

09:45.080 --> 09:48.750
♪ Once we played
in the heather ♪

09:48.830 --> 09:52.670
♪ Now I wonder if you ever ♪

09:52.750 --> 09:56.090
♪ Play in the heather ♪

09:56.170 --> 09:58.510
♪ On your own ♪

09:58.590 --> 10:01.220
[ Sobbing ]

10:01.300 --> 10:03.560
Does everyone here
know Susie?

10:03.640 --> 10:05.060
Yes, son.
Of course.

10:05.140 --> 10:08.810
We were all created the same way
you were -- gaseously.

10:08.890 --> 10:12.770
And we all felt the same
longing to hover around her head

10:12.860 --> 10:15.190
and haunt her waking hours.

10:15.280 --> 10:18.150
But it's better for us
to live here in the swamp.

10:18.240 --> 10:21.490
-Hmm.
-My dads are very smart.

10:21.570 --> 10:23.240
Hmm...

10:25.620 --> 10:28.500
Okay, now, you just let us know
if you need anything.

10:28.580 --> 10:30.750
We'll be right
upstairs, okay?

10:30.830 --> 10:32.540
Thanks, Dads.

10:34.460 --> 10:35.880
Thanks, Dads.

10:35.960 --> 10:37.630
I'm not gonna visit.

10:37.720 --> 10:39.340
-That's our girl!
-That's our girl!

10:39.430 --> 10:40.720
[ Door closes ]

10:40.800 --> 10:42.930
[ Owl hooting ]

10:46.600 --> 10:48.600
Hmm...

10:48.680 --> 10:50.810
Hmm...

10:50.900 --> 10:54.400
Hmm...

10:54.480 --> 10:56.230
Hmm...

10:56.320 --> 11:01.240
♪♪

11:01.320 --> 11:02.950
Susie?

11:06.790 --> 11:12.250
♪♪

11:12.330 --> 11:17.710
♪♪

11:17.800 --> 11:20.880
A raven who looks like
he knows a terrible secret.
